<br>
PoF drops off of two kinds of mobs in SolA: Lava Elemental (35ish) and Blazing Elementals (30ish).  <br>
<br>
Lava Elemental:  Found in the gnome area of Sol A.  You need to trigger two hidden levers to open a locked door and to open the drawbridge.  Use a map to find them, you'll need to walk through two walls.  The Lava Elemental is at neg100, neg950.  Its placeholder is a clockwork that wanders among four static clockwork spawns.  Attacking it will aggro the other 4 (in my experience) and will give a faction hit for gnomes.  Not sure how hard it hits, only killed one, and it didn't change my faction message.  It seems that PoF drops more often of the Lava Elemental than the Blazing, except that the Lava is a single spawn and unknown as to how often it spawns as opposed to it's PH.  I decided against this camp, but if you dont mind gnome faction hits and are high enough level to let them all beat on you while your pet takes care of the Lava, this is probably the faster route (statistically).<br>
<br>
Blazing Elementals:  Located in hidden passageway that can be acessed through a wall at neg100, neg700 or through a hole in the floor at neg100, neg750.  There are 2 static spawns, and one spawn that is a placeholder for the Efreeti (who drops Platinum armband).  The elementals spawn on a 20min. timer, and the Efreeti on a 1hour20min. timer.  I have heard of mages who got their PoF on their first kill, and others, like me, who camped for hours before it dropped.  I believe it is a &quot;rare&quot; drop off these guys.  <br>
<br>
While you are waiting, this is a great place to get plat and sell to the gnome vendor (assuming good faction) at neg300, neg1100.  Fine steel, gems (especially flame agate 7p!) and various other junk yeilded me about 500p a night for 3 nights of camping.  There are also 4 other &quot;boss mobs&quot; that I killed several times to get nice mid-level bazaar sellin' gear:  Goblin Captain at 100, neg700; Kindle at neg100, neg550; Kobold Predator at neg315, neg550; and Foreman down in the pit from the kobold predator hallway.<br>
<br>
Some misc info:<br>
<br>
At 51, everything aggro'd me, even the super duper green young goblins.  So kill everything you come across (except gnomes and clockworks) to avoid being ambushed by dumb greenies. <br>
<br>
During the last 4 hours of my camp, I was very burned out of killing goblins, so I just sat in the blazing hallway and came back every 20 min to check on my elementals.  Sitting in the middle of the hallway aggrod both elementals, so my pet killed them without me having to tell him to attack, and when I came to check, i'd usually have two dead elementals at my feet to loot (unless the corpses were empty).  So the last few hours I didn't much of anything except loot corpses and buff my pet every once in a while.<br>
<br>
Well, I hope this helps people who are venturing on their journey to SolA.  Don't give up! It *does* drop, and maybe you'll be one of the lucky ones to have it drop with the first mob. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
